---
// Privacy policy (EN) — GDPR. Reviewable base.
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../../config/site";

const c = SITE.company;
const cif = c.cif || "[tax ID pending]";
const address = c.address || "[registered address pending]";
const alternates = { es: "/privacidad", en: "/en/privacy", fr: "/fr/confidentialite" };
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy policy" description="How Calma Society handles your personal data." locale="en" alternates={alternates}>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-prosa px-5 pb-8 pt-12 sm:px-8 sm:pt-16">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-oro">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-4xl text-tinta sm:text-5xl">Privacy policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-piedra-suave">Last updated: June 2026</p>

    <div class="article-body mt-8">
      <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Controller:</strong> {c.legalName} (Tax ID {cif})</li>
        <li><strong>Address:</strong> {address}</li>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> {c.email} · <strong>Phone:</strong> {c.phone}</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. What data we process and why</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Newsletter subscription:</strong> your email address, to send you our content. Legal basis: your consent.</li>
        <li><strong>Contact form:</strong> your name, email and message, to answer your enquiry. Legal basis: your consent.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> technical and usage data in aggregate, anonymous form to run and improve the site. Legal basis: legitimate interest.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Retention</h2>
      <p>We keep your data while you remain subscribed or until you request deletion, and for any legally required periods.</p>

      <h2>4. Recipients and processors</h2>
      <p>We do not sell your data. We work with providers acting as data processors:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Formspree</strong> (handling contact form submissions).</li>
        <li><strong>MailerLite</strong> (newsletter management, when active).</li>
        <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> (hosting and content delivery).</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Some providers may process data outside the European Economic Area; where
        that happens, appropriate GDPR safeguards apply (e.g. standard contractual clauses).
      </p>

      <h2>5. Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        You may exercise your rights of access, rectification, erasure, objection,
        restriction and portability by writing to <strong>{c.email}</strong>. You can
        withdraw consent at any time (e.g. via the unsubscribe link in each
        newsletter) and lodge a complaint with the Spanish Data Protection Agency
        (<a href="https://www.aepd.es" rel="noopener" target="_blank">aepd.es</a>).
      </p>

      <h2>6. Security</h2>
      <p>We apply reasonable technical and organisational measures, and the site is always served over an encrypted (HTTPS) connection.</p>

      <h2>7. Minors</h2>
      <p>
        This site is not directed to children under 14. We do not knowingly collect
        data from minors without the consent of a parent or legal guardian.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy to reflect legal or service changes. The date of the
        last update is shown at the top.
      </p>

      <p>See also the <a href="/en/legal-notice">Legal notice</a> and <a href="/en/cookies">Cookie policy</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
